<item>
            <title>[LU-15900] hsm_control parameters shouldn&apos;t prevent mount</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15900</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the HSM parameter &lt;tt&gt;hsm_control&lt;/tt&gt; can be stored in config log to be set during mount process. Meanwhile if corresponding HSM state cannot be set, e.g. transition like &lt;tt&gt;stopped-&amp;gt;disabled&lt;/tt&gt; then it returns error and whole mount fails. Possible solution could be to report error about wrong state change but don&apos;t return error to don&apos;t affect mount process&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
